ifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nThis is session 68. It was a NO-OP session — the only work done was fixing the same state corruption for the 52nd time (stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverting from done to review because Ralph overwrites sprint-state.json with stale in-memory state).\n\nThe sprint is 100% complete: 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. Ralph must be stopped.\n\nProduce a retrospective covering:\n1. Session summary — no-op, state corruption fix #52\n2. Issues analysis — the recurring state corruption, token waste\n3. Cost analysis — from the cost report\n4. What went well — sprint complete\n5. What went wrong — 52 wasted sessions on the same bug\n6. Lessons learned\n7. Action items — stop Ralph, fix the stale-state overwrite bug\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a3eb6b9d536efdfe7","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\nSummary of findings:\n\n- **Session 68** was the 52nd consecutive no-op session fixing the same state corruption (stories 16-5/6/7/8 reverting from `done` to `review`)\n- **Sprint is 100% complete:** 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics\n- **Total cost:** $754.41 across 5,520 API calls\n- **Estimated waste:** ~$312 (42%) burned on 52 no-op sessions that produced zero value\n- **Root cause** (identified 51 sessions ago, never fixed): Ralph holds stale in-memory state and overwrites sprint-state.json on each loop, reverting completed stories\n- **Top action item:** Stop Ralph. The sprint is done. Every additional loop iteration wastes money fixing the